<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1720" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1720">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.812/122.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Jefferson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Presidential party and myself left Tuesday on United States ship <hi rend="italic">Chattanooga</hi> on trip of inspection of Fonseca Bay
                            and returned to Managua today. Trip a very instructive one and President
                            Díaz expressed himself as being unusually pleased with the opportunity
                            of visiting this much-discussed region and with the courtesy and
                            hospitality of Captain Senn. Nicaraguan people in general seem to be
                            deeply interested in the trip and greeted cordially on the way. I shall
                            report in detail by mail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>